3. About
--------

citygml-tools is a CLI program that bundles several operations for processing
CityGML files.

citygml-tools is built with citygml4j, the open source Java API for CityGML.


4. System requirements
----------------------

* Java JRE or JDK >= 1.8


5. How to use it
----------------

Open a shell environment and execute the citygml-tools script from the "bin"
folder to launch the program.

Use the following command to list the available operations:

    > citygml-tools --help

To display information about how to use a specific operation, type the
following:

    > citygml-tools help [operation]

On some UNIX/Linux distributions you will first have to set execution rights
for the start script. Change to the "bin" folder and enter the following to
make the start script executable for the owner of the file:

    > chmod u+x citygml-tools


